    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "You got what you asked for, they DID align, but you have different columns in a, b\nand you are effectively summing values + a `np.nan` (as you didn't tell pandas\nhow to fill the nan, which is implicity in `df1 + df2`)\n\nmaybe you _meant_ this?\n\n```\nIn [19]: times = date_range('now',periods=10)\n\nIn [20]: df1 = DataFrame(randn(10),columns=['A'],index=times)\n\nIn [21]: df2 = DataFrame(randn(10),columns=['B'],index=times)\n\nIn [24]: a,b = df1.align(df2,fill_value=0)\n\nIn [25]: a+b\nOut[25]: \n                            A         B\n2013-04-23 00:53:56 -1.616711  0.280222\n2013-04-24 00:53:56  0.448335 -0.165730\n2013-04-25 00:53:56 -0.522400 -1.013349\n2013-04-26 00:53:56 -2.087715 -0.696145\n2013-04-27 00:53:56  0.281090  0.005573\n2013-04-28 00:53:56  2.801685 -0.186990\n2013-04-29 00:53:56  0.974753 -0.135450\n2013-04-30 00:53:56  2.394150 -1.776405\n2013-05-01 00:53:56 -0.581694  0.635996\n2013-05-02 00:53:56 -1.336157  0.659597\n```\n"
